The illuminated crosshair sight is tucked in nicely next to the laser and is a natural alaignment with your eye.

6 clip side shell holder.

Mounted a delrin custom machined nose which extends past the barrel so you can store it muzzle down Rubber pads so when you lay it down , the sights do not touch the table.
Adjustable shoulder strap on swivels.
Adjustable stock with standard rubber shoulder pad.
Back - up flip sights front and rear.
Extra batteries for sights and allen keys store in grip handle base.

Why am I selling it. I am a small framed guy and with all the gizzmos it's a bit heavy for me to swing in the house ( home defence use ) A larger set guy or for general all use hunting it's good to go.
Only about maybe 50 rounds have gone through it.
weighs 9 1/2 lbs with 11 shells ( 5 in gun, 6 on clip )
Come with +/-200 rounds of mixed, slugs, buck and bird shot

This thing is seriously cool.
Perfect shape, better in person.
Many of the parts are custom machined to fit the best way.
Have all the origional stock parts if you want to go duck hunting.
Shoots perfect from the hip with the green laser beam sight.
I have many more pictures with good detail I can forward.
Nice piece of work that was fun to build.
Plan on doing the same thing to a kid's 20 Ga mossberg 

$500 OBO
Cash Please, No Trades

title: For Sale/Trade:  Vintage and German Mauser 8x57 ammo
postcontent: Been out there too long, will take best offer... There are 4 boxes of older Mauser 8x57 ammo. All of it was stored indoors and is in great condition for its age. Prices were set based on research of vintage ammo sites, catalogs and discussions, and yes i do know what a "new" box of 8x57 goes for. This is more on the collectable end rather than normal range fodder. Winchester 200g $50 IWI 197g $40 German brass $35 German steel $35 Will meet FTF along I95 in the Fredericksburg area or as far west as the Rt-17/Rt-29 intersection at Clark Bros and as this is ammo I will not ship due to the costs/restrictions. The first box is simple to identify, it is a complete red box of 60~70’s commercial Winchester Super Speed 8x57 Mauser 200g Stock #W8MM1. The box is in great shape for its age and has all 20 rounds. The second box is a about a 4x4x1 square cardboard box stamped 8x57 SP on one end and “for 98k Mauser action only” in red on the top, obviously this is a single box out of an over pack. The 18 rounds of ammo inside are dated 53 and the head stamp identifies them as IMI 8x57 Light Ball manufactured in Israel. Rumor in the blogosphere has it that this shoots well but is in the warm side. The last 2 are German war stock ball ammo dated 44; the labeling indicates that one in in brass case and the other in steel case. I believe there are 15 rounds per box. I opened to check for water damage and corrosion but that was it to avoid damaging the boxes (one already has a small tear from opening before I got them). To avoid the questions early there are no swastika, ss or deaths head stamps on any of the boxes. They appear to be for the general infantryman use out of an over pack, something that was apparently readily available post war. White label- brass case 15 Pâté S.m.E 1944 auy 14 Nz.Gew.BI.P.(2-2-0,45) ..1944rdl 21 Patron.1-5*-1944auy-Gesch.1944 auy 3bb 30/40 -1943 emp 393 Blue Stripe- steel case 15 Batronen S.m.E. 1944 eej. 10 Nz.Gew.BI.P.(2-2-0,45) ..1943/3 Patron.1-5*-1944auy-Gesch.1944 auy 3bb 30/40 -1943 emp 393
